1.  Place the vmware tools rpm package in a yum repo you have available to your systems
2.  Install this package :)

=How it works=
1.  Puts a hook in rc.local
2.  hook checks for the following:
   - verify runnign in a Vmware vm
    - is there a newer version of Vmware tools available?  
      -- if so install it
    - is there a file telling me current state  (/var/lib/vmtool-status)?
      -- if no, run vmware-config.pl
      -- if yes, verify uname -r matches the KERNEL line in /var/lib/vmtool
         -- if yes, exit
         -- if no,  run vmware-config and write out new /var/lib/vmtool-status



